RBS, Lehman Received $1.4 Billion From Formula One, Express Says

-- B y   T h o m a s   B i e s h e u v e l
-- 
2011-06-18T15:47:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-18/rbs-lehman-received-1-4-billion-from-formula-one-express-says.html
Royal Bank of Scotland Plc and
 Lehman Brothers Holdings Inc. (LEHMQ)  have received $1.4 billion in loan
repayments and interest from Formula One owner  CVC Capital
Partners , the Express reported, without saying how it obtained
the information.  Since CVC bought Formula One it has repaid $762.3 million
of its loans and paid $662.7 million in interest payments, the
newspaper said. In the same period, Formula One has made a net
profit of $1.2 billion the Express said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Thomas Biesheuvel in London at 
 tbiesheuvel@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Amanda Jordan at 
 ajordan11@bloomberg.net  